All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:

**Bug:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy) — skips the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — processes every element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Why it failed:** For an array of length `n`, the condition `i < n - 1` only iterates indices `0` through `n-2`, leaving the last element (index `n-1`) unprocessed. Removing the `- 1` makes the loop run through all indices including the last one.

